WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.680
Robbie, just me welcoming is absolutely wonderful.

00:04.480 --> 00:06.880
Richard and Marilyn bought it for me for my birthday.

00:08.400 --> 00:09.520
They're so thoughtful.

00:10.640 --> 00:13.360
You are very lucky Robbie to have such a nice family.

00:15.840 --> 00:18.640
You something wrong, Alexandra? No, nothing.

00:20.800 --> 00:22.320
Yes, there is. I can tell.

00:23.840 --> 00:29.120
What's the matter? Come on, you can tell me. What's up?

00:30.160 --> 00:33.520
I don't know. Something's wrong.

00:36.480 --> 00:37.520
Okay, let's talk.

00:41.680 --> 00:44.000
I received a letter from my parents this morning.

00:45.520 --> 00:48.000
Did they write some bad news? No.

00:49.520 --> 00:54.560
Well, then why are you so sad? I miss them. I miss them very much.

00:55.200 --> 00:57.200
Sorry, Alexandra.

00:58.880 --> 01:00.080
But I understand.

01:03.520 --> 01:05.520
The Moinas treat me so nicely.

01:06.160 --> 01:08.640
And I love being with your family so much.

01:11.440 --> 01:15.120
When I receive the letter with photographs of my family, I cried.

01:16.960 --> 01:18.560
I cried because I missed them all.

01:19.520 --> 01:22.000
You really miss your family, don't you? Yes.

01:22.320 --> 01:25.840
I know I must seem silly.

01:27.040 --> 01:28.560
It's not like I have nobody.

01:29.760 --> 01:33.280
I like the Moinas very much and they're so kind to me.

01:38.800 --> 01:43.120
Hey, why don't we go out for a cheeseburger and french fries? That'll cheer you up.

01:44.320 --> 01:45.760
And you can use my Walkman.

01:47.440 --> 01:48.480
That's a good idea.

01:49.120 --> 01:58.240
But if we go out, please don't complain about your math teacher or your math homework.

01:58.240 --> 01:59.680
I want to have fun.

01:59.680 --> 02:05.120
So do I. I have to turn off the lights or else my father would get really angry.

02:05.120 --> 02:07.200
He says I never turned them out when I leave.

02:08.720 --> 02:10.080
If they come home and they're on.

02:14.400 --> 02:16.880
Do you hear something? Yes, what was that?

02:18.640 --> 02:20.560
It sounded like a dog barking.

02:20.560 --> 02:23.840
Ah, sound like a dog barking right here.

02:23.840 --> 02:24.400
Yeah.

02:28.080 --> 02:29.120
A dog.

02:29.120 --> 02:30.560
A springer spaniel.

02:33.280 --> 02:34.800
Come on in, make yourself at home.

02:35.760 --> 02:37.440
Oh, you poor little thing.

02:38.480 --> 02:39.840
Come here. Come on.

02:48.560 --> 02:49.520
Poor baby.

02:50.800 --> 02:52.160
Where did you come from?

02:56.400 --> 02:57.360
And then Jenna.

02:58.320 --> 03:01.120
And she belongs to Mr. and Mrs. Levinson.

03:01.680 --> 03:02.640
There's a phone number.

03:03.920 --> 03:07.120
555-8448.

03:08.640 --> 03:10.320
Robbie, maybe you should call them.

03:11.040 --> 03:13.920
And tell the Levinson's we have their cute little spaniel.

03:14.560 --> 03:17.360
I've always wanted a springer spaniel. She's so cute.

03:18.480 --> 03:20.480
What?

03:35.200 --> 03:43.360
The number you are calling 555-8448 is no longer in service.

03:44.320 --> 03:48.320
The number's no longer in service.

03:51.120 --> 03:55.200
Oh, you poor baby. You lost your family.

03:56.320 --> 03:58.320
We'll find them. Don't worry, Alexandra.

04:13.360 --> 04:15.360
I'll be right back.

04:19.200 --> 04:21.760
Alexandra and I are such good friends.

04:21.760 --> 04:28.800
We listen to music together and go places together and talk about things like today.

04:28.800 --> 04:33.680
Alexandra was so unhappy and I didn't understand why at first.

04:33.680 --> 04:35.920
I received a letter from my parents this morning.

04:37.440 --> 04:38.880
Did they write some bad news?

04:39.680 --> 04:39.920
No.

04:40.400 --> 04:42.400
Why are you so sad?

04:42.880 --> 04:44.880
Then I realized that Alexandra was lonely.

04:44.880 --> 04:47.440
She was so lonely without her family.

04:47.440 --> 04:49.520
You really miss your family, don't you?

04:49.520 --> 04:50.560
Yes.

04:52.560 --> 04:54.560
I know I must seem silly.

04:54.560 --> 04:56.560
It's not like I have nobody.

04:57.600 --> 05:01.200
I like them, Alina, very much and they're so kind to me.

05:01.200 --> 05:03.200
She seemed so sad.

05:03.200 --> 05:05.200
I had to cheer her up.

05:05.200 --> 05:06.800
I got an idea.

05:07.600 --> 05:10.000
We always have such a good time when we go out together.

05:10.000 --> 05:13.600
Hey, why don't we go out for a cheeseburger and french fries?

05:13.600 --> 05:14.800
That'll cheer you up.

05:14.800 --> 05:16.800
But then Gemma showed up.

05:16.800 --> 05:18.000
I did!

05:18.000 --> 05:20.800
I think Alexandra felt better.

05:20.800 --> 05:23.600
She wasn't the only one who missed her family.

05:23.600 --> 05:25.200
Gemma did too.

05:25.200 --> 05:27.600
Gemma looked so lonely.

05:27.600 --> 05:29.600
It was such a sad face.

05:29.600 --> 05:31.600
And Alexandra understood it.

05:31.600 --> 05:33.600
Oh, you're pretty pretty.

05:33.600 --> 05:35.600
You've lost your family.

05:35.600 --> 05:37.600
Don't worry, Alexandra.

05:37.600 --> 05:39.600
We'll find them.

